      <file>projects/agent-framework-knowledge-r1/SPEC.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read CLAUDE.md §16 (Pointers — Where to find everything) to identify the right insertion row for an agent-framework entry — likely near the existing "Researcher subagent" or "Architecture (subsystems, design)" rows. Decide whether to add one row or two (one for the skill, one for the knowledge base)</step>
    <step>Edit root CLAUDE.md: add row(s) to the Pointers table linking (a) the new skill at .claude/skills/agent-framework-component/SKILL.md, (b) the knowledge base at knowledge/agent-framework/, and (c) NOTES.md as the Spaarke-grounded commentary entry</step>
    <step>Read .claude/skills/INDEX.md to find the right insertion point (alphabetical? by-category? mirror existing convention)</step>
    <step>Edit .claude/skills/INDEX.md: add the agent-framework-component skill entry with its description line + tags</step>
    <step>Read knowledge/REFRESH-LOG.md to identify the format used for completed projects vs. monthly refresh entries</step>
    <step>Edit knowledge/REFRESH-LOG.md: append a completion entry for agent-framework-knowledge-r1 — date completed, topics affected (agent-framework), files added (new samples count, new docs count, NOTES.md rewritten, INDEX.md added, skill + 5 patterns added), GAPs surfaced (forwarded to monthly refresh cadence)</step>
    <step>Also: add a row to .claude/CHANGELOG.md if the convention requires one for procedure-surface changes (per root CLAUDE.md §17 footer)</step>
    <step>Verify all linked paths in updated files resolve (Glob each new path)</step>
    <step>Commit: `docs(knowledge): wire agent-framework knowledge + skill into discoverability (R1 task 012)`</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
